#### Description of the project
- Introduction:
   - March 2024
   - The study focused on the impact of text features on job posting conversion rates. Various statistical and machine learning approaches were used. The best predictive capabilities were achieved using a pre-trained Bert and further data processing using CatBoost.
English version will be soon.
- Dataset:
- The recruiting agency provided full data of real IT job postings during previous year, including text descriptions and users activity.
- Business task
- For customer was important to predict will the response to the job posting be active

#### Main tools 
- Jupiter notebook, Python and Markdown
####  Machine Learning tools  
- ML models GridSearchCV, CatBoost, MultinomialNB, SGDClassifier
- For text extraction: CountVectorizer, TfidfVectorizer
- ML metrics f1_weighed 
#### Conclusions
- The project is completed
- For searching best hyperparameters used machine learning algorithm with pipeline, GridSearchCV.
- Machine learning models were trained and compared, the best model was selected
- The selected Machine learning model was tested on a test dataset
- report in PDF file

